<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Family Legal Strategy — Private & Confidential</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        :root {
            --ink: #1a1a2e;
            --ink-light: #3d3d5c;
            --ink-muted: #6b6b8a;
            --parchment: #faf9f7;
            --parchment-warm: #f5f0eb;
            --cream: #eee8e0;
            --gold: #b8860b;
            --gold-light: #d4a843;
            --gold-pale: #f0e6cc;
            --sage: #5a7a6a;
            --sage-light: #e8f0ec;
            --sage-dark: #3d5a4a;
            --rose: #8b4557;
            --rose-light: #f5e8ec;
            --rose-pale: #fdf5f7;
            --blue-steel: #4a6178;
            --blue-light: #e8eff5;
            --amber: #c47f17;
            --amber-light: #fef8eb;
            --shadow-soft: 0 1px 3px rgba(26,26,46,0.06);
            --shadow-med: 0 4px 12px rgba(26,26,46,0.08);
            --shadow-lg: 0 8px 30px rgba(26,26,46,0.12);
            --radius: 10px;
            --radius-sm: 6px;
        }

        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

        body {
            font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
            background: var(--parchment);
            color: var(--ink);
            line-height: 1.65;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        }

        .app {
            max-width: 1100px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            min-height: 100vh;
        }

        /* ─── Header ─── */
        .masthead {
            background: var(--ink);
            padding: 2.5rem 2rem 1.5rem;
            position: relative;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .masthead::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            top: -50%;
            right: -20%;
            width: 500px;
            height: 500px;
            background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(184,134,11,0.08) 0%, transparent 70%);
            pointer-events: none;
        }

        .masthead-badge {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            background: rgba(184,134,11,0.15);
            color: var(--gold-light);
            padding: 0.35rem 1rem;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.72rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: 1.5px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .masthead-badge::before {
            content: '🔒';
            font-size: 0.8rem;
        }

        .masthead h1 {
            font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
            color: #fff;
            font-size: 2rem;
            font-weight: 400;
            margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        }

        .masthead-sub {
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            font-weight: 300;
        }

        .masthead-sub strong {
            color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        /* ─── Navigation ─── */
        .nav {
            display: flex;
            background: #fff;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--cream);
            overflow-x: auto;
            scrollbar-width: none;
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 100;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
        }

        .nav::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }

        .nav-btn {
            background: none;
            border: none;
            padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
            font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
            font-size: 0.82rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            cursor: pointer;
            white-space: nowrap;
            position: relative;
            transition: color 0.25s;
        }

        .nav-btn:hover { color: var(--ink); }

        .nav-btn.active {
            color: var(--gold);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .nav-btn.active::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            left: 1rem;
            right: 1rem;
            height: 2.5px;
            background: var(--gold);
            border-radius: 2px 2px 0 0;
        }

        /* ─── Panels ─── */
        .panel {
            display: none;
            padding: 2rem;
            background: #fff;
            animation: panelIn 0.35s ease;
        }

        .panel.active { display: block; }

        @keyframes panelIn {
            from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px); }
            to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
        }

        /* ─── Typography ─── */
        .panel-title {
            font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            color: var(--ink);
            margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
            letter-spacing: -0.01em;
        }

        .panel-subtitle {
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            font-weight: 300;
        }

        .section-heading {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--ink);
            margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.6rem;
        }

        .section-heading .icon {
            width: 28px;
            height: 28px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .icon-gold { background: var(--gold-pale); }
        .icon-sage { background: var(--sage-light); }
        .icon-rose { background: var(--rose-light); }
        .icon-blue { background: var(--blue-light); }
        .icon-amber { background: var(--amber-light); }

        /* ─── Cards ─── */
        .card {
            background: var(--parchment);
            border: 1px solid var(--cream);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            padding: 1.25rem 1.4rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            transition: box-shadow 0.2s;
        }

        .card:hover { box-shadow: var(--shadow-med); }

        .card-header {
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: var(--ink);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
        }

        .card p, .card li {
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            color: var(--ink-light);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        .card ul {
            padding-left: 1.2rem;
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
        }

        .card li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }

        /* ─── Highlight Cards ─── */
        .highlight {
            border-left: 3px solid;
            padding-left: 1.2rem;
        }

        .highlight-gold { border-color: var(--gold); background: var(--gold-pale); }
        .highlight-sage { border-color: var(--sage); background: var(--sage-light); }
        .highlight-rose { border-color: var(--rose); background: var(--rose-light); }
        .highlight-blue { border-color: var(--blue-steel); background: var(--blue-light); }

        /* ─── Status Badges ─── */
        .badge {
            display: inline-flex;
            padding: 0.2rem 0.65rem;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: 0.5px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .badge-strong { background: var(--sage-light); color: var(--sage-dark); }
        .badge-caution { background: var(--amber-light); color: var(--amber); }
        .badge-critical { background: var(--rose-light); color: var(--rose); }
        .badge-info { background: var(--blue-light); color: var(--blue-steel); }

        /* ─── Checklists ─── */
        .checklist { list-style: none; padding: 0; }

        .checklist-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 0.75rem;
            padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
            background: var(--parchment);
            border: 1px solid var(--cream);
            border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.2s;
            user-select: none;
        }

        .checklist-item:hover {
            background: var(--parchment-warm);
            border-color: var(--gold-light);
        }

        .checklist-item.checked {
            background: var(--sage-light);
            border-color: var(--sage);
        }

        .checklist-item.checked .check-label {
            text-decoration: line-through;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
        }

        .check-box {
            width: 20px;
            height: 20px;
            border: 2px solid var(--cream);
            border-radius: 4px;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            margin-top: 1px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            transition: all 0.2s;
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            color: transparent;
        }

        .checklist-item.checked .check-box {
            background: var(--sage);
            border-color: var(--sage);
            color: #fff;
        }

        .check-label {
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            color: var(--ink-light);
            line-height: 1.5;
            flex: 1;
        }

        .check-label strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }

        .check-detail {
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            margin-top: 0.25rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        /* ─── Progress Bar ─── */
        .progress-container {
            background: var(--parchment);
            border: 1px solid var(--cream);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .progress-header {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
        }

        .progress-label {
            font-size: 0.82rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--ink);
        }

        .progress-count {
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
        }

        .progress-bar {
            height: 6px;
            background: var(--cream);
            border-radius: 3px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .progress-fill {
            height: 100%;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--sage), var(--sage-dark));
            border-radius: 3px;
            transition: width 0.4s ease;
        }

        /* ─── Timeline ─── */
        .timeline { position: relative; padding-left: 2rem; }

        .timeline::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            left: 8px;
            top: 0;
            bottom: 0;
            width: 2px;
            background: var(--cream);
        }

        .timeline-item {
            position: relative;
            padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .timeline-item::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            left: -2rem;
            top: 0.35rem;
            width: 12px;
            height: 12px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            border: 2px solid var(--gold);
            background: #fff;
        }

        .timeline-item.phase-active::before {
            background: var(--gold);
            box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px var(--gold-pale);
        }

        .timeline-phase {
            font-size: 0.72rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            color: var(--gold);
            margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
        }

        .timeline-title {
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: var(--ink);
            margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
        }

        .timeline-desc {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* ─── Comparison Grid ─── */
        .option-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 1rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        .option-card {
            border: 1px solid var(--cream);
            border-radius: var(--radius);
            padding: 1.3rem;
            background: #fff;
            position: relative;
            transition: all 0.2s;
        }

        .option-card:hover {
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-med);
            transform: translateY(-1px);
        }

        .option-card.recommended {
            border-color: var(--sage);
            background: var(--sage-light);
        }

        .option-card.recommended::before {
            content: '✦ RECOMMENDED';
            position: absolute;
            top: -0.5rem;
            right: 1rem;
            background: var(--sage);
            color: #fff;
            font-size: 0.62rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
            border-radius: 3px;
        }

        .option-name {
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 1rem;
            color: var(--ink);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .option-desc {
            font-size: 0.84rem;
            color: var(--ink-light);
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        }

        .pros-cons { font-size: 0.82rem; }

        .pro, .con {
            padding: 0.25rem 0;
            display: flex;
            gap: 0.4rem;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .pro::before {
            content: '✓';
            color: var(--sage);
            font-weight: 700;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .con::before {
            content: '✗';
            color: var(--rose);
            font-weight: 700;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        /* ─── Key Facts Box ─── */
        .facts-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
            gap: 0.75rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        .fact-item {
            background: var(--parchment);
            border: 1px solid var(--cream);
            border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
            padding: 1rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .fact-value {
            font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
            font-size: 1.4rem;
            color: var(--gold);
            margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
        }

        .fact-label {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            font-weight: 500;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.5px;
        }

        /* ─── Accordion ─── */
        .accordion-item {
            border: 1px solid var(--cream);
            border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .accordion-header {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
            background: var(--parchment);
            cursor: pointer;
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: var(--ink);
            transition: background 0.2s;
            user-select: none;
        }

        .accordion-header:hover { background: var(--parchment-warm); }

        .accordion-arrow {
            transition: transform 0.25s;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
        }

        .accordion-item.open .accordion-arrow { transform: rotate(180deg); }

        .accordion-body {
            max-height: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            transition: max-height 0.35s ease;
        }

        .accordion-body-inner {
            padding: 0 1.2rem 1.2rem;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            color: var(--ink-light);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        .accordion-body-inner ul {
            padding-left: 1.2rem;
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
        }

        .accordion-body-inner li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }

        /* ─── Disclaimer ─── */
        .disclaimer {
            margin-top: 2rem;
            padding: 1rem 1.3rem;
            background: var(--amber-light);
            border: 1px solid rgba(196,127,23,0.2);
            border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            color: var(--amber);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .disclaimer strong { color: #96650f; }

        /* ─── Footer ─── */
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 2rem;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--ink-muted);
            border-top: 1px solid var(--cream);
            background: #fff;
        }

        /* ─── Responsive ─── */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .masthead { padding: 1.5rem 1.2rem 1.2rem; }
            .masthead h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
            .panel { padding: 1.2rem; }
            .panel-title { font-size: 1.3rem; }
            .option-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .facts-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }

            .nav {
                flex-wrap: nowrap;
                overflow-x: auto;
                -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
            }

            .nav-btn {
                padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
                font-size: 0.76rem;
                min-height: 44px;
            }
        }

        @media (max-width: 480px) {
            .masthead h1 { font-size: 1.3rem; }
            .facts-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .nav-btn { font-size: 0.72rem; padding: 0.8rem 0.75rem; }
        }

        /* ─── Print ─── */
        @media print {
            .nav { display: none; }
            .panel { display: block !important; page-break-before: always; }
            .masthead { background: #333; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="app">
        <!-- ═══ MASTHEAD ═══ -->
        <div class="masthead">
            <div class="masthead-badge">Private & Confidential</div>
            <h1>Family Legal Strategy Dashboard</h1>
            <div class="masthead-sub">Prepared for <strong>Saima</strong> · Birmingham, England · Updated February 2026</div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══ NAVIGATION ═══ -->
        <div class="nav">
            <button class="nav-btn active" onclick="openPanel('overview')">Overview</button>
            <button class="nav-btn" onclick="openPanel('rights')">Legal Rights</button>
            <button class="nav-btn" onclick="openPanel('options')">Options & Pathways</button>
            <button class="nav-btn" onclick="openPanel('property')">Property & Finance</button>
            <button class="nav-btn" onclick="openPanel('children')">Children</button>
            <button class="nav-btn" onclick="openPanel('health')">Health Factor</button>
            <button class="nav-btn" onclick="openPanel('checklist')">Preparation Checklist</button>
            <button class="nav-btn" onclick="openPanel('timeline')">Strategic Timeline</button>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <!-- PANEL 1: OVERVIEW -->
        <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <div id="overview" class="panel active">
            <div class="panel-title">Situation Overview</div>
            <div class="panel-subtitle">A clear picture of where things stand and the strength of your position</div>

            <div class="facts-grid">
                <div class="fact-item">
                    <div class="fact-value">3</div>
                    <div class="fact-label">Children (14, 13, 9)</div>
                </div>
                <div class="fact-item">
                    <div class="fact-value">Primary</div>
                    <div class="fact-label">Carer Status</div>
                </div>
                <div class="fact-item">
                    <div class="fact-value">Active</div>
                    <div class="fact-label">Cancer Treatment</div>
                </div>
                <div class="fact-item">
                    <div class="fact-value">Strong</div>
                    <div class="fact-label">Legal Position</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section-heading">
                <span class="icon icon-gold">📋</span> Key Circumstances
            </div>

            <div class="card highlight highlight-gold">
                <div class="card-header">Your Situation at a Glance</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Location:</strong> Birmingham, England — governed by English family law</li>
                    <li><strong>Marriage:</strong> Long marriage with three dependent children</li>
                    <li><strong>Health:</strong> Currently mid-way through chemotherapy and immunotherapy for Grade 3 TNBC, awaiting mastectomy date</li>
                    <li><strong>Housing:</strong> Significant personal financial contributions to the family home (deposit, extensions, kitchen, legal fees)</li>
                    <li><strong>Asif's position:</strong> Remortgaged to fund improvements; likely to contest property ownership</li>
                    <li><strong>Children:</strong> All three would remain with Saima as primary carer</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section-heading">
                <span class="icon icon-sage">💪</span> Position Strength Assessment
            </div>

            <div class="card highlight highlight-sage">
                <div class="card-header">Why Your Position Is Legally Strong</div>
                <p>Under English family law, the court's <strong>first consideration</strong> is always the welfare of dependent children. Combined with your role as primary carer and your current medical treatment, the court is highly likely to prioritise:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Housing stability for the children</li>
                    <li>Protecting a medically vulnerable primary carer</li>
                    <li>Avoiding forced sale during active cancer treatment</li>
                    <li>Ensuring ongoing maintenance where income disparity exists</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--sage-dark);">This is not about using illness as leverage — it is about the court recognising legal reality and statutory factors under Section 25 of the Matrimonial Causes Act 1973.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="disclaimer">
                <strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> This dashboard is an informational strategy tool, not formal legal advice. It is prepared to help organise thinking and preparation before consulting a qualified family law solicitor. All decisions should be confirmed by a practising solicitor. Nothing in this document should be shared with the other party.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <!-- PANEL 2: LEGAL RIGHTS -->
        <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <div id="rights" class="panel">
            <div class="panel-title">Your Legal Rights</div>
            <div class="panel-subtitle">Understanding the law that protects you and the children</div>

            <div class="section-heading">
                <span class="icon icon-gold">⚖️</span> The Legal Framework
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">Matrimonial Causes Act 1973 — Section 25</div>
                <p>This is the law that governs how courts divide finances on divorce in England. The court <strong>must</strong> consider all of the following factors:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Welfare of children</strong> — this is the <em>first consideration</em></li>
                    <li><strong>Income and earning capacity</strong> of each party</li>
                    <li><strong>Financial needs and obligations</strong> of each party</li>
                    <li><strong>Standard of living</strong> during the marriage</li>
                    <li><strong>Age and health</strong> of each party</li>
                    <li><strong>Contributions</strong> — both financial and non-financial (including homemaking and childcare)</li>
                    <li><strong>Duration of the marriage</strong></li>
                    <li><strong>Conduct</strong> — only in exceptional cases</li>
                    <li><strong>Loss of benefits</strong> (e.g., pension) due to divorce</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section-heading">
                <span class="icon icon-sage">🏠</span> Housing Rights
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    Can he force me out of the house?
                    <span class="accordion-arrow">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="accordion-body-inner">
                        <strong>No.</strong> If you are a joint owner or a married spouse, you have a legal right to occupy the matrimonial home under the <strong>Family Law Act 1996</strong>. Even if the property is solely in his name, as a married spouse you have "home rights" — a right to live in the property that can be registered at the Land Registry.
                        <ul>
                            <li>He cannot change the locks or force you out.</li>
                            <li>He cannot sell or remortgage without your consent (if joint owner) or a court order.</li>
                            <li>If there is any risk of intimidation, a solicitor can apply for an <strong>Occupation Order</strong> to protect your right to remain.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    Does it matter who paid more into the house?
                    <span class="accordion-arrow">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="accordion-body-inner">
                        In a long marriage with children, the court generally treats the family home as a <strong>joint matrimonial asset</strong> regardless of who paid the deposit or funded renovations. However, your documented financial contributions (deposit, kitchen, extensions, legal fees) <strong>strengthen your negotiating position</strong> and demonstrate clear financial investment. The key factor the court considers is <strong>needs</strong> — particularly housing needs for the children — rather than a strict pound-for-pound audit.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    What about his remortgaging?
                    <span class="accordion-arrow">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="accordion-body-inner">
                        Remortgaging to fund family home improvements during the marriage means those funds were used for the <strong>joint benefit of the family</strong>. This does not give him a greater ownership claim. If he extracted equity for personal use outside the family, that could actually work <strong>against</strong> him — it could be characterised as financial irresponsibility or dissipation of assets.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    What maintenance am I entitled to?
                    <span class="accordion-arrow">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="accordion-body-inner">
                        Two separate types:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Child Maintenance:</strong> Calculated by the Child Maintenance Service (CMS) based on his gross income. For 3 children, approximately 19% of gross weekly income. This is separate from the divorce and runs independently.</li>
                            <li><strong>Spousal Maintenance:</strong> If there is a significant income gap, and especially if your earning capacity is reduced due to cancer treatment, the court can order ongoing maintenance. This is assessed case-by-case based on needs and ability to pay.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    What about Islamic divorce vs civil divorce?
                    <span class="accordion-arrow">▼</span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="accordion-body-inner">
                        These are two separate processes. An Islamic divorce (khula/talaq) does <strong>not</strong> dissolve a civil marriage. You would need to pursue a <strong>civil divorce</strong> through the courts to legally end the marriage and obtain financial orders. Both can proceed in parallel. Any Islamic mahr or financial obligations exist alongside civil law — the civil court may take note of them but is not bound by them.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

