                        <div class="check-label"><strong>Book initial consultation</strong> — Before any action or announcement</div>
                        <div class="check-detail">Take your financial summary and medical evidence. Ask about costs, timelines, and strategy.</div>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="checklist-item" onclick="toggleCheck(this)">
                    <div class="check-box">✓</div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="check-label"><strong>Check legal aid eligibility</strong> — Available in domestic abuse cases or exceptional circumstances</div>
                        <div class="check-detail">Legal aid is limited but available if there is evidence of domestic abuse (including financial control). Health circumstances may also support exceptional funding.</div>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="checklist-item" onclick="toggleCheck(this)">
                    <div class="check-box">✓</div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="check-label"><strong>Register Home Rights</strong> — If property is in his sole name, register your right at Land Registry</div>
                        <div class="check-detail">Prevents him from selling or remortgaging without your knowledge. Costs nothing via Form HR1.</div>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="checklist-item" onclick="toggleCheck(this)">
                    <div class="check-box">✓</div>
                    <div>
                        <div class="check-label"><strong>Understand the no-fault divorce process</strong> — Since April 2022, no blame needed</div>
                        <div class="check-detail">Application can be sole or joint. Minimum 20 weeks from application to conditional order, then 6 weeks to final order.</div>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Checklist progress is saved in your browser for this session. For security, do not use a shared or accessible device. This checklist does not transmit any data.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <!-- PANEL 8: STRATEGIC TIMELINE -->
        <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <div id="timeline" class="panel">
            <div class="panel-title">Strategic Timeline</div>
            <div class="panel-subtitle">A phased approach — preparation is silent power</div>

            <div class="card highlight highlight-gold" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
                <div class="card-header">⚡ Core Principle</div>
                <p><strong>Do not signal, threaten, or escalate.</strong> Quiet, thorough preparation creates the strongest possible position. Every step below can be completed without the other party's knowledge.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item phase-active">
                    <div class="timeline-phase">Phase 1 — Now (During Treatment)</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Silent Preparation</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">
                        Focus on medical treatment. In the background, begin gathering financial documents, property records, and evidence of contributions. Request medical letters confirming diagnosis and treatment. Do not mention divorce to Asif or mutual contacts. Build your information file quietly.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-phase">Phase 2 — When Ready</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Legal Consultation</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">
                        Meet a family law solicitor with your prepared documentation. Get a formal assessment of your position, likely outcomes, and costs. Ask about the no-fault divorce process, financial remedy options, and realistic timescales. This meeting is completely confidential.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-phase">Phase 3 — On Your Terms</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Initiate When Ready</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">
                        Only when you are medically and emotionally ready, and legally prepared, take formal steps. This might mean filing a divorce application, attending a MIAM, or instructing your solicitor to begin negotiations. The timing is entirely in your control.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-phase">Phase 4 — Process</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Divorce & Financial Proceedings</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">
                        The divorce itself is now largely administrative (no-fault). The key negotiation is the <strong>financial settlement</strong> — property, maintenance, pensions. If he cooperates: 6–9 months. If contested: 12–24 months. Your solicitor manages this process.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-phase">Phase 5 — Resolution</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Consent Order or Court Order</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">
                        The financial agreement is formalised as a <strong>Consent Order</strong> (if agreed) or a <strong>Financial Remedy Order</strong> (if the court decides). This is legally binding and enforceable. Child maintenance is handled separately via the CMS.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section-heading" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
                <span class="icon icon-rose">🚫</span> Critical Rules of Engagement
            </div>

            <div class="card highlight highlight-rose">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Do not</strong> threaten divorce or hint at leaving — this gives him time to prepare or move assets</li>
                    <li><strong>Do not</strong> move money out of joint accounts suddenly — this looks adversarial to the court</li>
                    <li><strong>Do not</strong> discuss plans with mutual friends or family who might inform him</li>
                    <li><strong>Do not</strong> leave the family home unless safety requires it — leaving can weaken a housing claim</li>
                    <li><strong>Do</strong> keep all communications civil and documented</li>
                    <li><strong>Do</strong> protect this dashboard and any notes — use a private device or password-protected folder</li>
                    <li><strong>Do</strong> confide only in trusted family (Iqra, Sajida) and your solicitor</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section-heading">
                <span class="icon icon-sage">📊</span> Realistic Outcome Range
            </div>

            <div class="option-grid">
                <div class="option-card recommended">
                    <div class="option-name">Best Case</div>
                    <div class="option-desc">House transferred to Saima or Mesher Order allowing her and children to remain. Larger equity share (60–65%). Spousal maintenance during and after treatment. Full child maintenance via CMS. Settlement by negotiation within 6–9 months.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="option-card">
                    <div class="option-name">Mid Case</div>
                    <div class="option-desc">Mesher Order — remain in home until youngest is 18 (2035). Equity split 55/45 in her favour. Child maintenance via CMS. Limited spousal maintenance. Process takes 9–15 months.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="option-grid" style="margin-top: 0;">
                <div class="option-card">
                    <div class="option-name">Contested Case</div>
                    <div class="option-desc">He refuses to cooperate. Full court proceedings required. Judge decides — health, children, and primary carer status still weigh heavily. Takes 18–24 months. Higher legal costs (£20,000+). Outcome still likely favourable given circumstances.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="option-card">
                    <div class="option-name">Least Favourable</div>
                    <div class="option-desc">House ordered sold. Even in this scenario, equity split adjusted in her favour due to needs. Court would still ensure adequate housing for children. Spousal and child maintenance orders remain available.</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="disclaimer">
                <strong>CONFIDENTIALITY NOTICE:</strong> This document is prepared solely for private strategic planning. It contains sensitive personal, medical, and financial information and should not be shared with, disclosed to, or accessible by the other party, mutual contacts, or any person not directly involved in providing legal advice. Store securely.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══ FOOTER ═══ -->
        <div class="footer">
            Prepared February 2026 · For private use only · Not formal legal advice · Consult a qualified solicitor before taking any action
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        // ─── Panel Navigation ───
        function openPanel(id) {
            document.querySelectorAll('.panel').forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));
            document.querySelectorAll('.nav-btn').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
            document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
            event.currentTarget.classList.add('active');
            window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
        }

        // ─── Checklist Toggle ───
        function toggleCheck(item) {
            item.classList.toggle('checked');
            updateProgress();
        }

        function updateProgress() {
            ['phase1', 'phase2', 'phase3'].forEach(phase => {
                const list = document.querySelector(`.checklist[data-phase="${phase}"]`);
                if (!list) return;
                const total = list.querySelectorAll('.checklist-item').length;
                const checked = list.querySelectorAll('.checklist-item.checked').length;
                const pct = total > 0 ? Math.round((checked / total) * 100) : 0;
                
                const countEl = document.getElementById(`count-${phase}`);
                const fillEl = document.getElementById(`fill-${phase}`);
                if (countEl) countEl.textContent = `${checked} / ${total}`;
                if (fillEl) fillEl.style.width = `${pct}%`;
            });
        }

        // ─── Accordion ───
        function toggleAccordion(header) {
            const item = header.parentElement;
            const body = item.querySelector('.accordion-body');
            const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
            
            // Close all in same panel
            item.closest('.panel').querySelectorAll('.accordion-item.open').forEach(ai => {
                ai.classList.remove('open');
                ai.querySelector('.accordion-body').style.maxHeight = '0';
            });
            
            if (!isOpen) {
                item.classList.add('open');
                body.style.maxHeight = body.scrollHeight + 'px';
            }
        }

        // ─── Touch-friendly: prevent double-tap zoom on buttons ───
        document.querySelectorAll('.nav-btn, .checklist-item, .accordion-header').forEach(el => {
            el.addEventListener('touchend', function(e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                this.click();
            });
        });

        // Init
        updateProgress();
    </script>
